-- Manchester City Ready to Sell Balotelli After Clash, Mail Says
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-01-05T14:58:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-05/manchester-city-ready-to-sell-balotelli-after-clash-mail-says.html
Manchester City is ready to sell
striker  Mario Balotelli  after his training ground clash with
manager Roberto Mancini two days ago, the Daily Mail said.  Though Mancini yesterday downplayed the altercation, the
manager has decided its time for Balotelli to go, the Mail said.
Mancini, who has previously stood by the 22-year old, has
finally accepted he has done all he can, the newpaper said.  City is willing to talk to any club that may wish to make
an offer, the Mail said. AC Milan has show interest in a loan
dael, but City wants a cash sale, the newspaper said.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  